    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Assessment / Exit Ticket</title>
        <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_5b8hevgn">
                <title>Exit Ticket Problems and Solutions</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_jfiu8eis">
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li xml:id="auto_t160ydf7">
                            <p xml:id="auto_v1mk6g2j">
                                <m>(x + 4)(x + 5)</m>: Expand to get <m>x^2 + 9x + 20 = 0</m>. Roots: <m>x = -4</m> and <m>x = -5</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_2yteez4z">
                            <p xml:id="auto_zx6y6u3v">
                                <m>(x + 3)^2</m>: Expand to get <m>x^2 + 6x + 9 = 0</m>. Root: <m>x = -3</m> (repeated).
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_jhsbz2lq">
                            <p xml:id="auto_dqhveqfu">
                                <m>4x^2 + 8x</m>: Set equal to zero, factor as <m>4x(x + 2) = 0</m>. Roots: <m>x = 0</m> or <m>x = -2</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_266q13pv">
                            <p xml:id="auto_ybquckjn">
                                <m>3x^2 + 6x</m>: Set equal to zero, factor as <m>3x(x + 2) = 0</m>. Roots: <m>x = 0</m> or <m>x = -2</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_9lo5o62i">
                            <p xml:id="auto_73c899gx">
                                <m>(p - q)(p - q)</m>: Expand to get <m>p^2 - 2pq + q^2 = 0</m>. Root: <m>p = q</m> (repeated).
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </li>
        </dl>
    </axiom>

     <exercises xml:id="exercises-formations-of-quadratic-equatiors-by-factors">
        <!--Exercises-->
        <exercise xml:id="auto_xz69nsjj">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_p7jv5aud">
                    Form quadratic expression using the following expressions.
                    <ol xml:id="auto_98tpp6a8" marker="(a).">
                              <li xml:id="auto_1wu5hggt">
                                       <p xml:id="auto_2g1iq3iw">                                    
                                         <m>(x + 4)(x + 5)</m>
                                      </p>
                                </li>
                                <li xml:id="auto_cg5mwzht">
                                      <p xml:id="auto_skluz2rr">
                                         <m>(x + 3)^2</m>  
                                      </p>
                                </li>
                                <li xml:id="auto_z1pi6k35">
                                    <p xml:id="auto_wpxmd106">
                                        <m>4x^2 + 8x</m>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li xml:id="auto_wlf2r6my">
                                    <p xml:id="auto_g4sw8kl5">
                                        <m>3x^2 + 6x</m>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li xml:id="auto_424ic9l7">
                                    <p xml:id="auto_zknudzfl">
                                        <m>(p - q)(p - q)</m>                                    
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li xml:id="auto_ig9285m0">
                                    <p xml:id="auto_yq4s2ed5">
                                        <m>(ax + b)(2ax - 3b)</m>                                    
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                    <li xml:id="auto_0ldv8zp7">
                                        <p xml:id="auto_7fc9d2wg">
                                            <m>(x - 8)(x + 8)</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li xml:id="auto_wdebhyew">
                                        <p xml:id="auto_fkj5mdhw">
                                            <m>(4 - 2x)(\frac{1}{2}x + 3)</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li xml:id="auto_0grhi3bi">
                                        <p xml:id="auto_y082ed4k">
                                            <m>(5dx + 3d)(2dx - 4d)</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li xml:id="auto_ey4guvrh">
                                        <p xml:id="auto_uvy50u3w">
                                            <m>(\frac{1}{2} + x)^2</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li xml:id="auto_faah5qai">
                                        <p xml:id="auto_c07po388">
                                            <m>(\frac{1}{8} + \frac{1}{x})^2</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
                <solution>
                <p xml:id="auto_pk83tplt">
                <ol  marker="(a)">
                    <li xml:id="auto_79zz8y5f">
                                <p xml:id="auto_agt2dwb2">
                                    To form a quadratic expression from the given expression, expand by multiplying terms in the first bracket with those in the second. Arrange as:
                                    <md>
                                        <mrow> (x+4)(x+5) \amp = x(x+5) +4(x+5)</mrow>
                                        <mrow> \amp = x^2 + 5x + 4x + 20</mrow>
                                        <mrow> \amp = x^2 + 9x + 20</mrow>
                                    </md>
                                </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_vmsrfx8g">
                        <p xml:id="auto_1gg6mzhp">
                            To form a quadratic expression from the given expression,first consider that this expression is a perfect square and for this reason the bracket is multiplied by twice itself. Arrange as:
                            <md>
                                <mrow> (x+3)^2 \amp = x(x+3) +3(x+3)</mrow>
                                <mrow> \amp = x^2 + 3x + 3x + 9</mrow>
                                <mrow> \amp = x^2 + 6x + 9</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_pn1kcl54">
                        <p xml:id="auto_1pkj1xlk">
                            To form a quadratic expression from the given expression,First make the equation to be equal to <m>0</m> then write it as:
                            <md>
                                <mrow> 4x^2 + 8x \amp = 0</mrow>
                                <mrow> 4x(x + 2x) \amp = 0</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_f4fscty6">
                        <p xml:id="auto_esdmptug">
                            To form a quadratic expression from the given expression,First make the equation to be equal to <m>0</m> then write it as:
                            <md>
                                <mrow> 3x^2 + 6x \amp = 0</mrow>
                                <mrow> 3x(x + 2) \amp = 0</mrow>
                            </md>  
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_8nxmwnry">
                        <p xml:id="auto_jsctuund">
                        To form aquadratic expression, multiply the terms in the first bracket with those in the second bracket. 
                        <md>
                            <mrow> (p-q)(p-q) \amp = p(p-q) - q(p-q)</mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp = p^2 - pq - pq + q^2 </mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp = p^2 - 2pq + q^2 </mrow>
                        </md> 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_tfhl5rah">
                        <p xml:id="auto_78352q2p">
                        To form aquadratic expression, multiply the terms in the first bracket with those in the second bracket. 
                        <md>
                            <mrow> (ax + b)(2ax - 3b) \amp = ax(2ax - 3b) + b(2ax - 3b)</mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp = 2a^2x^2 - 3abx + 2abx - 3b^2 </mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp = 2a^2x^2 - abx - 3b^2 </mrow>
                        </md> 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_4vr7ubns">
                        <p xml:id="auto_ixd85nt9">
                        To form aquadratic expression, multiply the terms in the first bracket with those in the second bracket. 
                        <md>
                            <mrow> (x - 8) (x + 8) \amp = x(x + 8) - 8(x + 8)</mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp = x^2 + 8x - 8x - 64 </mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp = x^2 - 64 </mrow>
                        </md> 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_5owd0tdd">
                        <p xml:id="auto_zuinuizb">
                        To form aquadratic expression, multiply the terms in the first bracket with those in the second bracket. 
                        <md>
                            <mrow> (4 - 2x) (\frac{1}{2}x + 3) \amp = 4(\frac{1}{2}x + 3) - 2x(\frac{1}{2}x + 3)</mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp = 2x + 12 - x^2 - 6x </mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp =  - x^2 - 4x + 12 </mrow>
                        </md> 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_6ey7jybo">
                            <p xml:id="auto_720w0neu">
                            To form aquadratic expression, multiply the terms in the first bracket with those in the second bracket. 
                            <md>
                                <mrow> (5dx + 3d)(2dx - 4d) \amp = 5dx(2dx - 4d) + 3d(2dx - 4d)</mrow>
                                <mrow> \amp = 10d^2x^2 - 20d^2x + 6d^2x - 12d^2 </mrow>
                                <mrow> \amp = 10d^2x^2 - 14d^2x - 12d^2 </mrow>
                            </md> 
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_lp9stvnd">
                            <p xml:id="auto_rkfaeb3t">
                                To form aquadratic expression, multiply the bracket by twice itself because it is a perfect square. 
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> (\frac{1}{2} + x)^2 \amp = (\frac{1}{2} + x)(\frac{1}{2} + x) </mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = \frac{1}{2}(\frac{1}{2} + x) + x(\frac{1}{2} + x)</mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = \frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{2}x + \frac{1}{2}x + x^2 </mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = x^2 + x + \frac{1}{4} </mrow>
                                </md> 
                            </p>
                        </li>
                                <li xml:id="auto_v7wddgd1">
                                <p xml:id="auto_5v2cr14x">
                                        To form aquadratic expression, multiply the bracket by twice itself because it is a perfect square. 
                                        <md>
                                            <mrow> (\frac{1}{8} + \frac{1}{x})^2 \amp = (\frac{1}{8} + \frac{1}{x})(\frac{1}{8} + \frac{1}{x}) </mrow> 
                                            <mrow> \amp = \frac{1}{8}(\frac{1}{8} + \frac{1}{x}) + \frac{1}{x}(\frac{1}{8} + \frac{1}{x})</mrow> 
                                            <mrow> \amp = \frac{1}{64} + \frac{1}{8x} + \frac{1}{8x} + \frac{1}{x^2} </mrow>
                                            <mrow> \amp = \frac{1}{x^2} + \frac{1}{4x} + \frac{1}{64} </mrow>
                                        </md> 
                                    </p>
                            </li>
                    </ol>  
                </p>
            </solution>
        </exercise>
    </exercises>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>
        <table xml:id="auto_flqe2oiw">
            <title>Differentiation strategies</title>
            <tabular halign="left">
                <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
                    <cell>Learner Group</cell>
                    <cell>Strategy</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Struggling Learners (Support)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line><alert>Scaffolding:</alert> Provide a step-by-step template for forming equations. Start with simple roots such as <m>x = 1</m> and <m>x = 2</m>. Use visual diagrams to show the link between roots and factors. Encourage verification by substituting roots back into the equation.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>On-Level Learners (Core)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line>The core lesson activities as described above.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Advanced Learners (Challenge)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line><alert>Extended Learning Experience:</alert> Form quadratic equations from the following: (a) Roots <m>x = \frac{1}{2}</m> and <m>x = -3</m>, (b) Roots <m>x = 2 + \sqrt{3}</m> and <m>x = 2 - \sqrt{3}</m>, (c) A rectangle has length <m>(x + 5)</m> and width <m>(x + 2)</m> with area 40, (d) Sum of roots is 7 and product is 12.</line>
                        <line><alert>Solutions:</alert> (a) <m>(x - \frac{1}{2})(x + 3) = 0</m>, multiply by 2: <m>(2x - 1)(x + 3) = 0 \rightarrow 2x^2 + 5x - 3 = 0</m>. (b) Sum <m>= 4</m>, product <m>= (2 + \sqrt{3})(2 - \sqrt{3}) = 1</m>, so <m>x^2 - 4x + 1 = 0</m>. (c) <m>(x + 5)(x + 2) = 40 \rightarrow x^2 + 7x + 10 = 40 \rightarrow x^2 + 7x - 30 = 0 \rightarrow (x + 10)(x - 3) = 0 \rightarrow x = 3</m>. (d) <m>x^2 - 7x + 12 = 0 \rightarrow (x - 3)(x - 4) = 0 \rightarrow x = 3, 4</m>.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>
    </axiom>
    <xi:include href="../../resources-assessment.ptx" />
    <xi:include href="../../resources-reflection.ptx"/>
</subsubsection>